title: Paper Doll, 1876–80
medium: Lithograph and brush and applied watercolors
description: Female paper doll with a small oval face and straight dark brown hair that is pulled back in a circular bun and held in place with a gold comb.  The doll is dressed in a petticoat, appropriate for the time period.

tombstone.epitaph:
Paper Doll, 1876–80.
1876–80. Lithograph and brush and applied watercolors. Gift of Grace Lincoln Temple. 1937-22-12.
